.TH "drm_atomic_helper_prepare_planes" 9 "drm_atomic_helper_prepare_planes" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_atomic_helper_prepare_planes \- prepare plane resources before commit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_atomic_helper_prepare_planes
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_atomic_state *state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "state" 12
atomic state object with new state structures
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function prepares plane state, specifically framebuffers, for the new
configuration, by calling \fIdrm_plane_helper_funcs.prepare_fb\fP. If any failure
is encountered this function will call \fIdrm_plane_helper_funcs.cleanup_fb\fP on
any already successfully prepared framebuffer.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error code on failure.
